Generate the private key using:
openssl genrsa -out private.pem 2048

Generate the public key using:
openssl rsa -in private.pem -pubout -out public.pem

Check for the key contents: (NOT A PART OF THIS PROCESS)
openssl rsa -in private.pem -text -noout
openssl rsa -in public.pem -pubin -text -noout

Write a new file:
echo HelloRSA > message.txt

Encrypt the file/anything:
openssl pkeyutl -encrypt -pubin -inkey public.pem -in message.txt -out message.enc


Decrypt it:
openssl pkeyutl -decrypt -inkey private.pem -in message.enc -out message.dec
